Class GnVideoLayer

java.lang.Object
  com.gracenote.gnsdk.GnObject
      com.gracenote.gnsdk.GnDataObject
          com.gracenote.gnsdk.GnVideoLayer

public class GnVideoLayer
extends GnDataObject

Both DVDs and Blu-ray Discs can be dual layer. These discs are only writable on one side of the disc, but contain two layers on that single side for writing data to. Dual-Layer recordable DVDs come in two formats: DVD-R DL and DVD+R DL. They can hold up to 8.5GB on the two layers. Dual-layer Blu-ray discs can store 50 GB of data (25GB on each layer)

videoRegion

public java.lang.String videoRegion()
Video product region value from the current type, e.g., 1. This is a list/locale dependent value.

Remarks:

This is a list-based value requiring that a list or locale be loaded into memory.

To render locale-dependent information for list-based values, the application must allocate a GnLocale object. A LocaleNotLoaded message is returned when locale information is not set prior to a request for a list-based value.
